### ── HEALTH ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Health
GET {{transactionServiceUrl}}/actuator/health


### ── CREATE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### Credit transaction  →  saves id and referenceNumber to variables
### Requires: account with id=1 exists and is ACTIVE (run account-service.http first)
# @name createCreditTransaction
POST {{transactionServiceUrl}}/api/v1/transactions
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "accountId": 1,
  "customerId": 1,
  "transactionType": "CREDIT",
  "amount": 2000.00,
  "currency": "EUR",
  "description": "Salary",
  "transactionDate": "2026-04-08T09:00:00Z"
}

> {%
  client.global.set("transactionId", response.body.id);
  client.global.set("referenceNumber", response.body.referenceNumber);
  client.test("201 Created", () => client.assert.response.status === 201);
%}


